fields.descriptive_line: Master bedroom accessories including a dresser and armoire, photographs and paintings, part of a dolls' house in the style of the 1940s made in England by Roma Hopkinson in the late 1980s to late 1990s
fields.physical_description:
[room setting] Master bedroom room setting with wood effect flooring and printed floral wallpaper. There are two light fixtures, a fan, two framed paintings and two framed photographs fixed to the walls. The room also contains a dresser with jewellery, toiletries, and a mirror, as well as an armoire with binoculars on top.
[beds (furniture)] Metal bedstead painted black and gold with a mattress, two pillows, sheets, blanket, and quilt.
[chests] Wooden chest with a hinged lid and two lower drawers. Attached to the top of the chest is a plastic paperweight and a shoehorn.
[end tables] Two green wicker armchairs with green and pink flower print seat cushions.
[tables (support furniture)] Green wicker end table with lifting lid and storage space inside.
[chests of drawers] Green wicker effect table with silver footed fruitbowl and fruits, and a pearl bracelet on a blue cushion.
[chairs] Tall chest of drawers with brass effect handles. The chest has three large drawers at the bottom and two small drawers side by side at the top. Fixed on top of the chest is a wooden wireless and four painted ceramic statues.
[fireplaces] Wooden armoire with mirrored door and a drawer at the bottom. On top is a painted ceramic vase and bust.
[tables (support furniture)] Wooden armchair with cream satin seat.
[chests of drawers] Black metal fireplace with grate. On top of the mantlepiece is a silver clock and two models of dogs.
[tables (support furniture)] Wooden bedside table or worktable with a single pedestal leg. On top of the table is a round paperweight with shells inside and a gold perfume bottle. The table has a single drawer which contains a lift-out tray holding reels of cotton thread and a sheet of miniature buttons. Beneath the drawer is a pink slide out compartment containing a piece of embroidery.
[carpets] Wooden chest of drawers with five drawers increasing in depth. On top of the chest is a green ceramic vase in the shape of a fish with its mouth open and a book opened on 'Sherlock Holmes'.
[dolls' house accessories] Wooden bedside table with single top drawer and low shelf. On top of the table is a working lamp, wristwatch, Bible, glass with false teeth, and a circular picture frame on a metal stand. On the shelf below is a model of a gondola made from metal.
[dolls' house clothing] Two tapestry carpets for the master bedroom. The larger carpet has a yellow border with pink flowers and green foliage in the centre. The smaller carpet is maroon and green.
[chairs] Dolls' house accessories for the master bedroom including two suitcases, a wooden trunk, metal space heater, chamber pot, gas mask in a box, hot water bottle, beige handbag, torch, two books, two garment boxes, black handbag and gloves, a framed photograph, two ceramic model dogs, a book showing Queen Mary's Dollhouse, a flag, and a set of unframed photographs.

fields.public_access_description: This house is a replica of a real house in Surrey where Roma Hopkinson lived with her family during the Second World War. Roma built this house in the 1980's, paying incredible attention to detail, reproducing ration books, identity cards, newspapers, and photo albums by reducing copies of the original versions. The photographs show her family as they appeared at that time. Each doll is also modelled on a family member with Roma appearing as one on of the children in a school dress. The house accurately reflects the wartime era, showing popular products, foodstuffs, games, and furnishings from the time.
